{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895991589,"sessionID":"ses_28459dc2effe3ell0hCbULiGub","part":{"id":"prt_d7ba654f8001lHmw19uW4SwpOh","messageID":"msg_d7ba649e50012t1ginun7WJIbo","sessionID":"ses_28459dc2effe3ell0hCbULiGub","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-1de7a4378c0942358262071746d5c023","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/sdk-python/tests/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/sdk-python/tests/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-040: Python SDK/CLI Tests\n2: \n3: **Module**: sdk-python/tests\n4: **Language**: Python\n5: **Size**: M\n6: **Design**: [Stage ST-3 completed]\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Overview\n11: Create comprehensive test coverage for the AgentCube Python SDK and CLI components. Tasks are organized by module and should be completed in the order listed, as some tasks may have dependencies.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Phase 1: Core SDK Infrastructure Tests\n16: \n17: ### Task 1.1: SDK Test Infrastructure Setup\n18: - [ ] Create test utilities module (`tests/fixtures/`) with common fixtures\n19: - [ ] Configure pytest settings for SDK tests (pytest.ini or pyproject.toml)\n20: - [ ] Set up test coverage configuration (coverage.py)\n21: - [ ] Create conftest.py with shared fixtures for:\n22:   - Mock HTTP clients\n23:   - Mock Kubernetes API clients\n24:   - Temporary directories/workspaces\n25:   - Sample test data\n26: \n27: **Verification**: Run `pytest tests/ -v` with 0 tests passing (infrastructure ready)\n28: \n29: ---\n30: \n31: ### Task 1.2: HTTP Client Tests\n32: - [ ] Create `tests/test_http_client.py`\n33: - [ ] Test HTTP client initialization with default and custom timeouts\n34: - [ ] Test GET requests with query parameters\n35: - [ ] Test POST requests with JSON payload\n36: - [ ] Test PUT requests with JSON payload\n37: - [ ] Test DELETE requests\n38: - [ ] Test error handling (404, 500, connection errors)\n39: - [ ] Test retry logic for transient failures\n40: - [ ] Test custom headers support\n41: \n42: **Verification**: `pytest tests/test_http_client.py` - all tests pass\n43: \n44: ---\n45: \n46: ### Task 1.3: Logging Utilities Tests\n47: - [ ] Create `tests/test_log_utils.py`\n48: - [ ] Test logger initialization with different log levels\n49: - [ ] Test verbose mode logging\n50: - [ ] Test logging with custom formatters\n51: - [ ] Test logging to file handlers\n52: - [ ] Test log filtering\n53: \n54: **Verification**: `pytest tests/test_log_utils.py` - all tests pass\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: ### Task 1.4: General Utilities Tests (Expansion)\n59: - [ ] Expand `tests/test_utils.py`\n60: - [ ] Test URL validation and normalization\n61: - [ ] Test configuration file parsing (YAML/JSON)\n62: - [ ] Test environment variable resolution\n63: - [ ] Test timeout parameter conversion\n64: - [ ] Test version string parsing and comparison\n65: \n66: **Verification**: `pytest tests/test_utils.py` - all tests pass\n67: \n68: ---\n69: \n70: ## Phase 2: Core SDK Client Tests\n71: \n72: ### Task 2.1: Control Plane Client Tests\n73: - [ ] Review and expand `tests/test_control_plane_client.py`\n74: - [ ] Test agent registration\n75: - [ ] Test agent listing with filters\n76: - [ ] Test agent status retrieval\n77: - [ ] Test agent deletion\n78: - [ ] Test error handling for non-existent agents\n79: - [ ] Test pagination for list operations\n80: \n81: **Verification**: `pytest tests/test_control_plane_client.py` - all tests pass\n82: \n83: ---\n84: \n85: ### Task 2.2: AgentRuntime Client Tests (Enhancement)\n86: - [ ] Review and expand `tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py`\n87: - [ ] Test session management (create, retrieve, delete)\n88: - [ ] Test invoke with various payload types\n89: - [ ] Test invoke timeout behavior\n90: - [ ] Test concurrent invoke operations\n91: - [ ] Test session cleanup on context exit\n92: - [ ] Test verbose logging in runtime operations\n93: \n94: **Verification**: `pytest tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py` - all tests pass\n95: \n96: ---\n97: \n98: ### Task 2.3: AgentRuntime Data Plane Client Tests\n99: - [ ] Review and expand `tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane_client.py`\n100: - [ ] Test bootstrap session creation\n101: - [ ] Test invoke with streaming responses\n102: - [ ] Test invoke with large payloads\n103: - [ ] Test connection error recovery\n104: - [ ] Test data plane authentication\n105: \n106: **Verification**: `pytest tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane_client.py` - all tests pass\n107: \n108: ---\n109: \n110: ### Task 2.4: CodeInterpreter Client Tests (Enhancement)\n111: - [ ] Review and expand `tests/test_code_interpreter_client.py`\n112: - [ ] Test code execution with Python code\n113: - [ ] Test file upload and download operations\n114: - [ ] Test session state management\n115: - [ ] Test error handling for syntax errors\n116: - [ ] Test resource cleanup\n117: \n118: **Verification**: `pytest tests/test_code_interpreter_client.py` - all tests pass\n119: \n120: ---\n121: \n122: ### Task 2.5: CodeInterpreter Data Plane Client Tests\n123: - [ ] Review and expand `tests/test_code_interpreter_data_plane_client.py`\n124: - [ ] Test code execution requests\n125: - [ ] Test file upload streaming\n126: - [ ] Test file download streaming\n127: - [ ] Test execution timeout handling\n128: - [ ] Test progress reporting\n129: \n130: **Verification**: `pytest tests/test_code_interpreter_data_plane_client.py` - all tests pass\n131: \n132: ---\n133: \n134: ### Task 2.6: Exception Handling Tests\n135: - [ ] Review and expand `tests/test_exceptions.py`\n136: - [ ] Test all custom exception types\n137: - [ ] Test exception message formatting\n138: - [ ] Test exception chaining\n139: - [ ] Test error code mapping\n140: - [ ] Test user-friendly error messages\n141: \n142: **Verification**: `pytest tests/test_exceptions.py` - al