ests pass (`pytest tests/integration/ -m integration`)\n565: - [ ] Test coverage meets minimum threshold (≥80% for SDK, ≥75% for CLI)\n566: - [ ] All tests have proper docstrings\n567: - [ ] All tests use appropriate fixtures\n568: - [ ] No flaky or non-deterministic tests\n569: - [ ] Test documentation complete\n570: - [ ] CI/CD integration for tests configured\n571: \n572: ### Final Verification\n573: Run the complete test suite:\n574: ```bash\n575: # Unit tests\n576: pytest tests/ cmd/cli/tests/ -v\n577: \n578: # Integration tests\n579: pytest tests/integration/ -m integration -v\n580: \n581: # Coverage report\n582: pytest --cov=agentcube --cov=cmd/cli --cov-report=html --cov-report=term\n583: ```\n584: \n585: All tests must pass with acceptable coverage.\n586: \n587: ---\n588: \n589: ## Notes\n590: \n591: ### Test Dependencies\n592: - pytest >= 7.0.0\n593: - pytest-cov >= 4.0.0\n594: - pytest-mock >= 3.10.0\n595: - pytest-asyncio >= 0.21.0 (if async tests needed)\n596: \n597: ### Integration Test Requirements\n598: - Docker daemon running (for build tests)\n599: - Kubernetes cluster access (optional, for K8s provider tests)\n600: - Mock services can be used for most integration tests\n601: \n602: ### Test Naming Conventions\n603: - Test files: `test_<module_name>.py`\n604: - Test classes: `Test<ClassName>`\n605: - Test functions: `test_<functionality>[_<condition>]`\n606: \n607: ### Mocking Strategy\n608: - Use `unittest.mock` for external dependencies\n609: - Use `pytest-mock` for cleaner mock fixtures\n610: - Keep mocks minimal and focused\n611: - Avoid mocking the system under test\n\n(End of file - total 611 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-040: Python SDK/CLI Tests\n\n**Module**: sdk-python/tests\n**Language**: Python\n**Size**: M\n**Design**: [Stage ST-3 completed]\n\n---\n\n## Overview\nCreate comprehensive test coverage for the AgentCube Python SDK and CLI components. Tasks are organized by module and should be completed in the order liste